      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(gateway): add image.providers RPC",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdd read-only `image.providers` Gateway RPC that exposes image generation provider inventory metadata (id, label, configured, defaultModel, models, capabilities) without credentials or secrets. Follows the same pattern as `tts.providers`.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add `image.providers` to Gateway core descriptors (operator.read scope)\n- Create `imageHandlers` module following `tts.providers` pattern\n- Register lazy handler in `server-methods.ts`\n- Add protocol schema and validator in `gateway-protocol` package\n- Handler validates response against schema before returning to client\n- Export schema through `./schema` barrel (per ClawSweeper finding 6)\n- Add 4 focused test cases (per ClawSweeper P2 requirement)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Exposes image generation provider inventory metadata over Gateway RPC for control UIs without spawning CLI process.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw setup with image generation providers configured.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n```bash\npnpm build\npnpm openclaw gateway call image.providers\n```\n\n**Environment metadata:**\n- Git commit: ccfb7fd8acf8cdd75e8fba54bc98cd3d75573ccb\n- Node: v22.19.0\n- OS: Darwin 24.6.0\n- OpenClaw: built from local checkout\n\n**Actual JSON output:**\n```json\n{\n  \"providers\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"openai\",\n      \"label\": \"OpenAI\",\n      \"configured\": true,\n      \"defaultModel\": \"dall-e-3\",\n      \"models\": [\"dall-e-2\", \"dall-e-3\"],\n      \"capabilities\": {\n        \"generate\": { \"enabled\": true },\n        \"edit\": { \"enabled\": false },\n        \"geometry\": false,\n        \"output\": [\"png\"]\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"active\": null\n}\n```\n\n**Observed result:** Successfully returns provider array. `active` field resolved from `agents.defaults.imageGenerationModel.primary`; returns `null` when not configured. Handler validates response against `ImageProvidersResultSchema` before responding; validation failure returns `INVALID_REQUEST` error code.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm build` passes\n- `pnpm tsgo:core` passes (noUnusedParameters clean)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/image.test.ts` passes (4 test cases)\n\n## Risk assessment\n\n- **merge-risk: auth-provider** — This RPC is read-only and does not modify OAuth/token/credential paths. The `configured` field uses `provider.isConfigured()` real readiness semantics (no `startsWith` auth-profile guessing). The `active` field is derived strictly from `agents.defaults.imageGenerationModel.primary` and returns `null` when unset (no fallback invention).\n\n- **merge-risk: compatibility** — Pure additive change (+409/-0). No existing RPC modified. Schema is exported through both `./index` (types) and `./schema` (schema barrel). Schema fields aligned with `src/image-generation/types.ts` including `edit.maxInputImages`, `geometry.aspectRatiosByModel`, `geometry.resolutionsByModel`.\n\n## Related\n\n- Fixes #78330\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
